      "section_title": "Introduction",
      "keywords": ["stack"],
      "content": "A Stack is a linear data structure that follows the Last In First Out (LIFO) principle."
    },
    {
      "section_title": "What is a Stack?",
      "keywords": ["definition"],
      "content": "A stack is a collection of elements where insertion and deletion occur at one end called the top."
    },
    {
      "section_title": "LIFO Principle",
      "keywords": ["lifo"],
      "content": "The last element inserted into the stack is the first element removed."
    },
